    heroTitle: "This is my personal website all about me",

    introBio: "Lauren is an aspiring electrical engineering student minoring in psychology, pursuing a future career as a patent attorney. She is committed to understanding how innovation, law, and mental health intersect—particularly in addressing systemic barriers that contribute to cyclical unhousement and difficult reintegration experiences. She is also expanding her nonprofit, Project Mosaic, which organizes monthly donation drives to directly support underserved communities.",

    aboutDescription: "This website serves as both a professional portfolio and a mission-driven platform aligned with my goal of becoming a patent attorney with a background in electrical engineering and psychology. It highlights my technical development, analytical thinking, and growing interest in intellectual property law, while also sharing structured resources intended to support marginalized communities. The site is designed for recruiters, internship coordinators, practicum instructors, future law school admissions committees, and community partners.",

