    personalStoryTitle: "Personal Story",
    personalStoryParagraph1: "My path toward advocacy began long before I had the language to describe it. Growing up in Los Angeles as the daughter of immigrant parents, I witnessed both the quiet sacrifices that sustain families and the structural barriers that often go unseen by others. Early mornings in my father’s car, long afternoons waiting after school, and weekends spent alongside my parents at work taught me discipline, patience, and deep respect for resilience.",
    personalStory2: "As I grew older, the disparities in my community became impossible to ignore—from unhoused neighbors at freeway exits to families navigating systems not built for them. Rather than allowing these realities to become background noise, I began transforming observation into action through academic focus and community work, including the expansion of Project Mosaic.",
    lessonsCarried: "Today, I carry forward the lessons my parents modeled: that dignity should never depend on circumstance, and that meaningful change requires both technical knowledge and sustained advocacy. My work reflects a long-term commitment to advancing equitable access, protecting innovation responsibly, and ensuring that the communities that shaped me are never overlooked.",

    prioritiesTitle: "Current Priorities & Focus Areas",
