    impactImages: "Impact Images",
    impactDescription: "The impact images on my personal branding website offer a visual narrative of my commitment to community-centered action. Rather than presenting service as abstract intention, these photographs document moments of direct engagement—from organizing donations to delivering essential supplies. Together, they illustrate how my work through Project Mosaic and related initiatives translates values into visible, measurable efforts that prioritize dignity, accessibility, and care.",

    viewProjectMosaicImpact: "<strong>Project Mosaic Impact</strong>",
    viewProjectPulmonaryImpact: "<strong>Project Pulmonary Lynwood Impact</strong>",

    nonprofitInfo: "Through Project Mosaic and Project Pulmonary, these efforts have resulted in tangible support for communities and frontline workers. From distributing food to local organizations to using over $100 in raised funds to provide hydration and snacks for firefighters, each initiative reflects my belief that small, coordinated actions can produce meaningful change. These projects demonstrate not only leadership and organization, but a sustained commitment to turning awareness into real-world impact.",
    exploreGallery: "Gallery",
    moreInfo: "This gallery highlights the breadth of my involvement across academic, service, and leadership spaces. From cohort-based programs like the Riordan Scholars Program and my internship with YMHA to school and community initiatives, each image represents a moment of active participation and growth. While this is only a snapshot of my work, visitors can explore many additional initiatives in my Projects tab, resume, and LinkedIn. I selected these moments intentionally to offer a meaningful glimpse into the environments and communities that shape my journey.",
    contributionsText: "Across these initiatives, my contributions have supported both immediate community needs and long-term capacity building. Whether creating empowerment content for Project Glimmer’s Girls’ Empowerment Academy, participating in the AIDS Walk Los Angeles through NHS, tutoring K–4 students, or helping lead fundraisers benefiting immigrant families and Guatemalan youth, my focus remains consistent: turning involvement into measurable support. Our food bank work alone helped package 77,656 pounds of produce for distribution to families in need, and my formal induction as NHS Treasurer reflects the trust placed in my leadership and accountability. Collectively, these efforts reinforce my ultimate goal of uplifting and supporting marginalized communities and communities in need.",
  
    mentorshipTitle: "Mentorship",
    mentorshipIntro: "Mentorship has been a quiet but powerful force in my growth, and this section highlights two of the many individuals who have guided me along my journey. While I have been fortunate to learn from a broader network of educators and professionals, I selected these mentors to offer a focused glimpse into the relationships that have most directly shaped my academic and career direction. Their support reflects the importance of intergenerational knowledge-sharing in expanding access, confidence, and opportunity.",

